frameDefinitions: These are words relating to filling containers and covering areas with some thing, things or substance, the Theme.
A Self-moving Escapee departs from an Undesirable_location.
An Agent manipulates a Fastener to open or close a Containing_object (e.g. coat, jar).
An Item comes to be attached to a Goal, with a Connector forming a bond between the Handle of the Item and the Goal (or some part of it).
The Fastener is an artifact created to close a Container (e.g. coat, jar).
An Agent causes a Useful_location to become accessible (or non-accessible) to a Theme to a certain Degree.
frameExamples: Lionel Hutz <t>coated</t> the wall with paint.
Mary <t>closed</t> her coat with a belt.
According to plan, the front part of the hull quietly <t>attached</t> to the docking gear.
The door <t>seal</t> prevented air from getting in and the kids' screams from getting out.
They've <t>blockaded</t> the entrance -- no one can get in or out.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> is the actor who instigates the filling.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the physical object or substance which changes location.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is the area or container being filled. Goal is generally the NP Object in this frame.
An event which brings about the filling of the <fen>Goal</fen>.
When the filling occurs.
Where the filling takes place.
The <fen>Escapee</fen> manages to leave the <fen>Undesirable_location</fen>.
The <fex name='Undesirable_location'>Undesirable_location</fex> is where the Escapee begins.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the escaping occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the Escaping occurs.

This role identifies the item that is closed by the agent with the fastener.
<fex name='Agent'>Lee</fex> <t>buttoned</t> <fex name='Containing_object'>his coat</fex>.
The Agent opens/closes the Containing-object.
This role identifies the fastener that the agent manipulates.
This role identifies the active zone of the container that may be expressed as the direct object of the target verb.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> closes the <fen>Container_portal</fen> or the <fen>Containing_object</fen>.
The location where the closing event takes place.
<fen>Connector</fen> identifies the  instrument used to attach, usually in a <ment>with</ment>-PP.
<fen>Item</fen> identifies the entity that comes to be attached to the <fen>Goal</fen>.
<fen>Items</fen> identifies the plural items that are tied together, resulting in their mutual attachment.
<fen>Goal</fen> identifies the location to which the first <fen>Item</fen> is attached.
The time when the attaching event takes place.
The location where the attaching event takes place.
This role identifies the item that is closed with the <fen>Fastener</fen>.
The artifact created to close a <fen>Container</fen>.
This role identifies the active zone of the container where the <fen>Fastener</fen> is located.
The <fen>Agent</fen> blocks access to the <fen>Useful_location</fen>.
The <fen>Useful_location</fen> is the place the <fen>Theme</fen> is headed towards and the <fen>Agent</fen> has changed the accessibility of.

The <fen>Agent</fen> may regulate access to the <fen>Useful_location</fen> by regulating access to a <fen>Portal</fen>, including a part of the portal that could block potential <fen>Theme</fen>s, such as doors or gates.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> changes the accessibility of the <fen>Useful_location</fen>.
The general <fen>Place</fen> where the blocking or allowing of access occurs.
listRoleExamples: Rev. Lovejoy carefully brushed the rolls <fex>with butter</fex>.
<fex>Benjamin</fex> escaped from Germany.
Benjamin escaped <fex> from Germany</fex>.
<fex>Harry</fex> uncorked the champagne.
Marcus tied his shoe <fex>with the neon-green shoelaces</fex>.
We zipped <fex>the tent flap</fex>.
They close the bank vault <fex>at precisely 5:35PM</fex>.
Shouldn't you have buttoned that <fex>in the bathroom</fex>?
The remoras attach to the whale <fex>with their strong jaws</fex>.
<fex>Remoras</fex> attached to the dolphins.
<fex>The cells</fex> bind together.
The remoras attach <fex>to the underside of the whale</fex>.
On Friday night, many men will simply elect to remove their tie and unbutton their top <fex>shirt</fex> button.
Man, I have just bought the exact same belt <fex><t>buckle</t></fex> and it won't open.
We couldn't close the <fex>tent flap</fex> zipper and a lot of flies came in .
<fex>Police</fex> have cordoned off the area where the crime took place.
Protestors barricaded <fex>a highway that connects the industrial sectors to the ports</fex>.
They've blockaded <fex>the entrance</fex> -- no one can get in or out.
A rebel group blockaded the roadways <fex>late last night</fex>.
Many roads were cordorned off <fex>in the central district</fex> right after the incident.
